Vice President Biden will be traveling to Brussels, Belgium, and Madrid, Spain, from May 5-8, 2010. During his visit, he will deliver a speech to the European Parliament and meet with leaders and representatives of the European Union institutions to discuss cooperation on counter-terrorism and other areas of mutual concern. He will also discuss trans-Atlantic security issues with NATO officials and meet with Belgian leaders. In Madrid, he will meet with King Juan Carlos, President Zapatero, and other members of the Spanish government to discuss bilateral issues, the Spanish Presidency of the EU, and ongoing cooperation on global challenges. More details about the trip will be released later.